metric.definition:
The metric tensor defines the geometry of spacetime. It allows calculation of distances, angles, and curvature. It relates coordinate intervals (dx^{\mu}) to the invariant spacetime interval (ds^2): ds^2 = g_{\mu
u} dx^{\mu} dx^{
u}.

